'''William George Searle''' was a 19th-century historian and fellow of [[Queens' College, Cambridge|Queens' College]], [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]],<ref>{{cite web|title=William George Searle: Historical papers|url=http://janus.lib.cam.ac.uk/db/node.xsp?id=EAD%2FGBR%2F0012%2FMS%20Add.5983-5986%2C%206599-6602%20and%206951-6954|publisher=janus.lib.cam.ac.uk|accessdate=6 December 2013}}</ref> on which he published a history.<ref>{{cite web|title=Queens' College chronology|url=http://www.queens.cam.ac.uk/page-239|publisher=queens.cam.ac.uk|accessdate=6 December 2013}}</ref>

His works include ''Ingulf and the Historia Croylandensis'', ''Onomasticon Anglo-Saxonicum: A List of Anglo-Saxon Proper'' and ''Anglo-Saxon Bishops, Kings and Nobles''.

